1
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:43,720
Why do you want to return to PD?

2
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,520
<i>Because I'm certain</i>

3
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,440
<i>the real culprit is still there.</i>

4
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:51,400
<i>Chakrit? If anything happens</i>
<i>to Mr. Praphop,</i>

5
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:53,440
<i>I will never forgive any of you.</i>

6
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,640
I take full responsibility.

7
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,480
<i>It's on you, Din.</i>

8
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,240
<i>The more you hurt me,</i>

9
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:01,880
<i>the more I'll hurt you, a hundred times,</i>
<i>a thousand times more.</i>

10
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:07,920
<i>Baicha…</i>

11
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,479
I'm sorry for everything.

12
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:18,200
Din! Let go of me!

13
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,200
I want to die!

14
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,240
Didn't you hear what your sister said?!

15
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:25,160
Baicha loves you so much.
Are you going to leave her all alone?!

16
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,080
Let go of me, Din!

17
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,360
- Krit!
- I won't.

18
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:31,680
- Krit!
- Let go.

19
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:33,520
Krit!

20
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:45,520
- Din!
- Mr. Din!

21
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,480
How are you?

22
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:19,000
Well… Just a minor scrape.

23
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:25,080
Not really worth
all the tears you shed for me.

24
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:29,640
Still joking at a time like this.

25
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,280
It's okay.

26
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,960
I'm ready to go, officers.

27
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:42,720
Wait, Chakrit.

28
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:50,120
Feeling sorry for me now?

29
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,120
I was already prepared.

30
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,840
If Praphop died,

31
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,680
I'd be charged

32
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,280
and sent to prison.

33
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,480
But if he didn't die,

34
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,240
then I'd be the one who would.

35
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:10,400
I just don't know when
he'll send someone to finish me off.

36
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:21,760
You won't die. Believe me.

37
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,560
But before you go,
I want to ask you something.

38
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,840
Did you send someone

39
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,080
to silence the housekeeper
you hired to drug me?

40
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,680
I never sent anyone.

41
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:39,520
That's what I thought.

42
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,680
I just wanted to be sure.

43
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,400
Oh?

44
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,280
If Krit didn't do it,

45
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,240
then who hired them?

46
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,640
Is something wrong, Din?

47
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,840
What are you all doing here?

48
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:06,240
Get out right now.
I don't want to see anyone.

49
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:10,440
We just want to talk to Uncle.

50
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,160
Talk to Mr. Praphop?

51
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,080
In his condition?
How could you even talk to him?

52
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,760
What are you doing?

53
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,520
Why take out that pin?

54
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:28,120
I just want to prove something.

55
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,360
I’m going to pierce your skin, Uncle.

56
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:43,960
Don't!

57
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,960
I really am going to do it.

58
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,160
Hey! Are you insane?

59
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,120
Chakrit already told me everything.

60
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,040
Ouch.

61
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,960
- Hey!
- You!

62
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:11,880
If you're going to do this,
make sure I die.

63
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,680
If I survive,

64
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:16,880
I'll make you suffer worse than death.

65
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:33,120
<i>He said that when he hit you,</i>

66
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,840
<i>you weren't breathing anymore.</i>

67
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:38,720
<i>He was shocked too</i>
<i>when he learned that you're still alive.</i>

68
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:42,360
He thought you'd be
in a coma for a long time.

69
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,240
But the truth is,

70
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:48,160
Chakrit was fooled
from the very beginning.

71
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,600
Everything happened so fast.

72
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,520
I never thought he'd dare hurt me.

73
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,280
And I'm already old.

74
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,600
There was no way I could fight back.

75
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,080
So, you held your breath

76
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,680
to survive, didn't you?

77
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,520
Yes.

78
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:15,720
But Chakrit had already planned
to frame you.

79
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,240
So, he didn't check carefully.

80
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:20,000
When he saw me not breathing,

81
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,640
he just shoved me into the car.

82
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,800
Serves him right.
No one can save stupidity.

83
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:29,640
Your instincts are incredible, Uncle.

84
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:34,760
But why pretend to be in a coma?

85
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,320
Wouldn't that risky, Ms. Rosarin?

86
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:45,360
If we get caught,
my reputation would be ruined.

87
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:48,400
But I'm this hospital's major shareholder.

88
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,160
Between losing your reputation

89
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:54,520
and getting fired on the spot,

90
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,160
you choose, Mr. Director.

91
00:07:57,200 --> 00:08:00,680
Yes, Ms. Rosarin. I'll take care of it.

92
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,760
Everything is under control.

93
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:26,560
Thank you for talking to him for me.

94
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,120
I couldn't have handled it myself.

95
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,080
My head's still pounding.

96
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:35,159
Can I ask you something, honestly?

97
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,080
Why did you do all this,

98
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:40,600
instead of just dealing
with Chakrit directly?

99
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,600
Chakrit is nothing.

100
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,280
I can deal with him anytime.

101
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:48,400
But if we got Din sent to prison first,

102
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:51,920
that would be killing
two birds with one stone.

103
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:53,560
Oh.

104
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,840
You really are something…

105
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,760
Impressive.

106
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:06,160
You actually managed to uncover the truth.

107
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,040
When did you figure it out?

108
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:14,520
From the moment you asked

109
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,960
to buy my shares, Auntie.

110
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:23,000
Alright. I agree.

111
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,240
- Thank you so much--
- Not yet.

112
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,960
I'm not helping for free.

113
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:34,520
All the PD shares you currently hold…

114
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,640
If you sell them to me, I'll help.

115
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:43,840
If I were you,
with my husband lying in a coma,

116
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:47,920
I wouldn't be in the mood
to worry about buying shares.

117
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:48,840
Right?

118
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,480
And another thing.

119
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,240
You were nearly beaten to death,

120
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,480
yet Nina, your only daughter,

121
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,760
didn't rush back from the U.S.

122
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,640
That's when I knew

123
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:05,760
this wasn't just between me and Chakrit.

124
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:09,360
Exactly. Even if Nina had work,

125
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:11,480
if something this serious happened,

126
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,800
she would've come back.

127
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,040
Yes.

128
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:17,280
The day I caught the man Chakrit sent

129
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:20,320
to attack Uncle Praphop at the hospital,

130
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:23,480
I took advantage of the moment
when Uncle let his guard down

131
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,320
to confirm it with my own eyes.

132
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:31,320
Nam. Go on ahead. I'll catch up.

133
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:34,240
Where are you going?

134
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,440
Just taking care of something.

135
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:00,120
Sir, are you alright?

136
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,640
I'm fine.

137
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:12,240
Why are you good at everything, Din?

138
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,640
Such a shame, isn't it?

139
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,880
That both Din and Krit are still alive.

140
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:24,040
If they were both dead,
everything would be so much easier.

141
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,200
What are you saying, Nam?

142
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:29,920
I already got Din's shares.

143
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,000
What's so difficult now?

144
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,880
Aren't you afraid of going to prison?

145
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:38,080
What you've done

146
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,320
is absolutely despicable.

147
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,240
Yeah.

148
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:42,880
Of course I am.

149
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,760
I'm so afraid,

150
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,560
I can barely stop laughing.

151
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,120
So?

152
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,840
Did you bring the police with you?

153
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,120
If you didn't,

154
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,160
it'll be hard to send me to prison.

155
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:01,640
So, if I did bring the police,

156
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:04,320
you'd confess to everything?

157
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,000
Din.

158
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:20,000
Were you secretly recording me?

159
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,800
Give it to me!

160
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:27,400
You think you're the only one
who knows how to stack plans on plans?

161
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:29,840
Din.

162
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,720
Your crimes include

163
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,720
fabricating evidence

164
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,200
and conspiracy to commit murder.

165
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:46,360
I'd say those two charges alone
are serious enough.

166
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,560
Looks like you'll be busy
sorting this out for a long time.

167
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,160
Damn you…

168
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,120
What do you want?

169
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:57,400
Want your shares back?

170
00:12:57,920 --> 00:13:01,800
Oh? The shares you two staged
this whole thing to trick me into selling?

171
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,000
I don't mind them.

172
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,200
And I don't want them back.

173
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,760
What I want

174
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:12,320
is the truth to come out.

175
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,280
Whoever committed any crimes

176
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:17,040
should face the consequences.

177
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,240
And Chakrit shouldn't be punished

178
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,520
for what he didn't do either.

179
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:31,440
I'd like to invite you to give
your statement at the station.

180
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:51,080
May I speak with Mr. Pathawee
for a moment?

181
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,200
It's fine, Officer.

182
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:05,000
Why did you help me?

183
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:08,800
I didn't really want to.

184
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,680
You slapped my woman.

185
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:15,880
You grazed my arm with a bullet.

186
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,560
You should've been killed
by Uncle Praphop.

187
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:25,000
Is that what you wanted to hear?

188
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:29,320
I just wanted the truth exposed.

189
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,760
I didn't want you to take
the blame for more than you did.

190
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,360
Nothing more than that.

191
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:45,600
I'm not angry at you, Chakrit.

192
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,720
And I don't resent you

193
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,960
to the point of wishing
a terrible ending on you.

194
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:57,200
We've already lost far too much.

195
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,040
Take care of Baicha for me.

196
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:08,920
Don't worry.

197
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:12,880
I love Baicha like my own sister.

198
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,960
She won't suffer. I promise.

199
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:25,760
If you ever make my sister cry,

200
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:29,160
I'll come after you.

201
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,920
If Baicha ever cries,

202
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:36,720
they'll be tears of happiness,

203
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,440
not sadness.

204
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,840
I love you, Krit.

205
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,560
I love you too, Baicha.

206
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:12,000
I'm sorry.

207
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,400
Mr. Chakrit.

208
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:20,800
This way, please.

209
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,800
Din.

210
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:23,240
Nina?

211
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:32,880
Thank you, Din.

212
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,640
Let's get straight to it.

213
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:39,840
My parents are now the major shareholders,

214
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,000
so I'll be taking over the company myself.

215
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:45,720
What do you think?

216
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:50,480
If you want me to step down,

217
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,800
I don't have a problem with that.
It's up to you.

218
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:57,520
Just like that?

219
00:17:58,560 --> 00:17:59,960
It's over for me.

220
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,800
Whenever you're ready, just let me know.

221
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,120
I'll resign myself.

222
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,640
The coffee's really good today.

223
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:21,720
No wonder Father always said
you're the most capable one.

224
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:25,320
You even remembered
that I like my coffee sweet,

225
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,920
not bitter.

226
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:28,560
That's good.

227
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:31,960
I like people
who understand things easily.

228
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,560
Not really, Nina.

229
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:37,520
I'm actually slow to understand.

230
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,280
By the time I finally do,

231
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:42,480
a lot has already been lost.

232
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,680
Are you trying to tell me something?

233
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,680
What I'm saying is…

234
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:51,360
After everything that's happened,

235
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:53,360
I've learned that

236
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,720
the most valuable thing

237
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:58,400
is people who are sincere with us.

238
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,080
Not the company.

239
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,280
And I hope

240
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,320
that one day,

241
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:08,760
you'll understand that too.

242
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,000
Should we get these boxes
loaded into your car?

243
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,920
Yes, please.

244
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,080
What are you looking at?

245
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:56,960
Just… looking around, that's all.

246
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,640
I thought you were taking it all in,

247
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:04,320
since you're about to be unemployed.

248
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:08,000
So good at teasing, huh?

249
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,640
What's this?

250
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:21,400
PD GROUP
RESIGNATION LETTER

251
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,280
You resigned?

252
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:27,400
Do you remember what I told you?

253
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:31,600
I'll be with you

254
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,800
through thick and thin.

255
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,320
So…

256
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:39,320
I'm not letting you lose your job alone.

257
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:43,240
So you're becoming unemployed with me?

258
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:46,040
Yes.

259
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,960
You fought for so long.

260
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:55,600
Why give up so easily?

261
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:59,280
Didn't you promise Uncle Tesho

262
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,080
you'd protect PD Group?

263
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,360
I already did.

264
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,840
The company

265
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,560
is still running.

266
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:11,160
Yo's and Nam's shares are still intact.

267
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:14,200
I only lost a little of my own.
I don't see that as losing.

268
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:19,000
Don't you regret it?

269
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:24,560
I spent almost my whole life there.

270
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:28,360
It does sting a bit to let go.

271
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,120
But I don't regret it.

272
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,720
I've got other projects I want to do.

273
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,320
Really?

274
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:38,960
Then,

275
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:42,400
can I be the first employee
of your new company?

276
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:45,360
When did I ever say
I was starting a new company?

277
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:47,320
What? Well,

278
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:50,720
you said you had other projects in mind.

279
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:55,840
The project I meant

280
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,680
is winning you back.

281
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:08,320
What are you talking about?
That makes no sense.

282
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,120
Sara.

283
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,480
Do you still want to be my first employee?

284
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:17,880
I can't hear you.

285
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:39,840
Nam… Nam…

286
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,560
My stomach hurts.

287
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:45,160
What, Baicha?

288
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:47,560
My stomach hurts.

289
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:50,160
I think the baby's coming.

290
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,480
Huh?

291
00:22:52,560 --> 00:22:53,800
Is it now?

292
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:01,560
Din! Din! Help! Something's up!

293
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,960
Din! Din!

294
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:05,600
Nam…

295
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,200
- What? Why are you yelling?
- Well…

296
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:08,360
What is it?!

297
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,120
It's Baicha. She's going into labor!

298
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,120
Huh?!

299
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,440
Then what are you waiting for?
Take her to the hospital!

300
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:21,040
- Yeah, the hospital!
- What? Who is it? Why the hospital?

301
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:22,080
- Mom.
- Huh?

302
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:24,840
Your grandchild is about to be born!

303
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:27,520
Huh? Baicha's in labor?

304
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:30,840
Easy, easy.

305
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:32,640
Slowly, yeah.

306
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,600
Mr. Nam, is the car ready?

307
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:37,960
I'm getting it right now.

308
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:39,520
Nam! Nam!

309
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:41,160
The car key's here!

310
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:45,560
Go, go, go.

311
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:47,640
My makeup bag though?

312
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:50,800
If I'm browless in the photos,
my fans will freak out.

313
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:53,760
I forgot it. Can we just use
an app to fix your brows later?

314
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:55,160
Nam.

315
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:57,040
Go get it for Baicha right now.

316
00:23:57,120 --> 00:23:58,320
But it's upstairs, Mom!

317
00:23:58,920 --> 00:23:59,760
Don't upset your wife.

318
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:04,760
- I'll get the car ready. Go grab it.
- Easy, easy. Go on.

319
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:07,400
- Go, go, go.
- Careful, dear. Slowly.

320
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:09,360
Slowly. Careful.

321
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:10,920
Almost there.

322
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:15,320
Do you think the baby will like my gift?

323
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,920
I even bought a teddy bear.

324
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:19,920
You're really asking this

325
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,920
about a baby less than 24 hours old?

326
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,480
Why? I can't ask?

327
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:28,040
If the baby can answer,
then go ahead and ask.

328
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:30,480
Don't be sarcastic.

329
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,720
I've never bought a gift
for a little child before.

330
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:34,160
It's normal to worry.

331
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:37,640
By little, you mean really little.

332
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:40,560
This is a newborn baby,
not a five-year-old.

333
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:43,760
And that teddy bear you bought
might not even get used right away.

334
00:24:43,840 --> 00:24:45,960
Honestly, in a month or so,

335
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:48,360
it'll probably end up in storage.

336
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:49,880
That's so mean.

337
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,760
Can't help it. You should've
asked me before buying it.

338
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:56,920
Okay then…

339
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,480
Next time, will you help me pick one?

340
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,640
Well… If I'm free.

341
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,120
Then that's great.

342
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:11,960
Because you probably know best
what our child would like.

343
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:17,080
Dream on.

344
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:29,720
So, the new supplier we just signed

345
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:31,680
are supplying other companies too?

346
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:33,840
Yes.

347
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,680
How could they do that?

348
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:37,840
They said they'd supply us exclusively.

349
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:40,560
They said another team did this

350
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:43,160
and asked me to apologize to you.

351
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:45,520
They promised it won't happen again.

352
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:46,840
How is that acceptable?

353
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:50,320
We're losing our advantage like this,
after what we put into the deal.

354
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:54,560
They're playing smart,
supplying our competitors

355
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:56,520
and blaming another team.

356
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:59,320
That's clearly a betrayal!

357
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:05,200
Hey.

358
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:08,080
What about the old supplier
Mr. Pathawee worked with?

359
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,760
Can we contact them again?

360
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:13,000
After you canceled the contract,

361
00:26:13,080 --> 00:26:15,040
they signed with another company.

362
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:17,920
And they're supplying
only that company now.

363
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:19,680
What a mess!

364
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:31,160
Who made this coffee?

365
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:32,880
I told you I like it sweet.

366
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:35,000
Why is it so bitter?

367
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:49,000
Hello!

368
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:51,720
Today, meet Baicha and Mommy…

369
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:53,400
- Namnuan!
- Yay!

370
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:56,920
Today,

371
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:59,640
I've got something exciting to share.

372
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:01,400
What is it, dear?

373
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:04,400
It's our new organic cream set

374
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:06,160
from the Sarah brand!

375
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:08,440
- Let me see!
- Here!

376
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:13,280
Hey.

377
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:16,400
How much did you pay
these two influencers?

378
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:17,960
The same rate as me?

379
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:22,800
They're paid with
Sarah brand's products for life.

380
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:24,440
So generous.

381
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:28,400
I'm the CEO. I need to have a big heart.

382
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:32,000
Just not big enough to include me, huh?

383
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,920
Trust me, okay?

384
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:42,520
I've already tried Sarah's products.

385
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,640
Oh my, my skin… I'm telling you.

386
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:48,640
<i>It's so bouncy. Just like a baby's!</i>

387
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:51,640
"I won't believe it

388
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,880
until I see how bouncy it really is."

389
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:55,920
Oh?

390
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,760
Yo! Yo!

391
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:01,360
Yo, you've got to trust me.
When you're back from New Zealand,

392
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:03,640
I'll let you touch my skin.

393
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,520
It's really bouncy.

394
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:09,640
"Is it bouncy for real,
or bouncy like Moo Deng?"

395
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:11,320
<i>That's Sarach.</i>

396
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:12,320
<i>Sarach?</i>

397
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:15,120
Oh, Sarach wants to know
what kind of bouncy it is?

398
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:16,720
Come here. I'll show you.

399
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,440
- Bouncy like this, sweetheart!
- Wow.

400
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:23,640
Boing, boing!

401
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:26,040
- Like this, bounce with Mommy!
- Wow, it really is bouncy!

402
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:28,440
<i>Boing, boing!</i>

403
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:33,040
- Boing, boing!
- Mom!

404
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,800
How am I supposed to go back now?

405
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,880
- Boing, boing!
- Mom's bouncing so hard!

406
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,400
- Boing, boing!
- What so funny?

407
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:42,240
- You think that's funny?
- Hey, hey, don't be violent! Wait.

408
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:45,360
Her dance is cute. Why are you so serious?

409
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:50,800
Hey, how about letting your dad
have a dance battle with my mom?

410
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,720
Yeah.

411
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,440
That actually sounds fun. Good idea.

412
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:57,520
- You little…
- Boing, boing!

413
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:18,440
Bouncy, right?

414
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:35,520
The first-week sales aren't bad.

415
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:39,280
They're lower than the first
product launch I did for PD,

416
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:42,200
but compared to a new company like PS,

417
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:45,040
the numbers are pretty strong.

418
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:48,760
And…

419
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:50,600
this is only online marketing.

420
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:51,800
We haven't gone offline yet.

421
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,680
I think we should try

422
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:55,480
setting up booths at events.

423
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:57,720
That should help boost brand awareness.

424
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:00,280
Okay.

425
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:03,400
I'll do more research on that.

426
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:10,680
Hey.

427
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:11,640
Wait.

428
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:14,840
Why are you leaning so close to me?

429
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:16,840
I'm just

430
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,200
leaning in to pressure the CEO

431
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,600
into giving me a raise.

432
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:25,040
I'm saving up
for something important right now,

433
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:26,600
but my salary

434
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,160
is basically minimum wage.

435
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:30,080
It's really not enough.

436
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:32,800
You're a new employee,

437
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:35,480
with no experience in this role,

438
00:30:35,560 --> 00:30:37,200
and you're still on probation.

439
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:40,200
Once you pass probation,

440
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:42,680
I'll reconsider, okay?

441
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:46,440
Yes,

442
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:47,880
Madam CEO.

443
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:53,880
Then this intern

444
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:56,000
will go order more snacks.

445
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,440
I'd love that.

446
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:15,160
‪EYES

447
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:20,000
Ms. Eyes?

448
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,000
I heard Eyes called you urgently?

449
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:30,640
Mhm.

450
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:33,320
She asked me to help check out the venue

451
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:35,000
and pick invitation cards.

452
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:37,680
She sent tons of designs.

453
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:41,800
Not sure why she'd ask you to choose.

454
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:51,160
I mean, what if you don't pick
what she likes?

455
00:31:51,240 --> 00:31:53,000
No other intention, really.

456
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:56,280
Yeah, I thought so too.

457
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:59,840
But in the end,

458
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:01,480
it's the bride's call anyway.

459
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:03,880
She probably already has a vision in mind.

460
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,120
No point arguing.

461
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:06,840
So…

462
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,080
When is she coming?

463
00:32:08,680 --> 00:32:09,640
She's on her way.

464
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:12,160
- Right now?
- And you…

465
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:14,720
- You're coming with me too.
- For what?

466
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:17,440
To help think things through together.

467
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:35,960
Dad.

468
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,080
Sara.

469
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:41,520
Hold on.

470
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:44,360
What is it, dear?

471
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:48,600
Are you leaving already?

472
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:49,720
Want me to walk you out?

473
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:51,160
No need.

474
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:54,000
Din asked Permboon to take me.

475
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:04,760
Can you stay a bit longer?

476
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:08,080
I haven't even had

477
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,280
a proper hug yet.

478
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:15,040
Did you fight with Din?

479
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,000
Not at all.

480
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:26,760
Be careful. If you keep
playing hard to get,

481
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:28,880
and one day he gives up on you,

482
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:32,440
don't say I didn't warn you.

483
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:51,200
I'll place the chairs here.

484
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:53,160
The layout will be circular,

485
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:55,800
and this area will be left open
for the dance floor.

486
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,760
You saw the photos I sent, right?

487
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:00,400
A small circle inside a bigger one.

488
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:01,840
I did.

489
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:04,160
But the problem is,

490
00:34:04,240 --> 00:34:07,160
don't forget the guests
will be dancing too.

491
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:10,760
But right now, the chairs
are taking up too much space.

492
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,760
I'm worried the floor won't be big enough.

493
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:15,760
Then why don't you try dancing with me?

494
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:17,840
Me?

495
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:18,880
Yes. Come on.

496
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:22,800
That way, we'll know
how much space we really need.

497
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:25,920
Alright.

498
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,159
Let's try.

499
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,520
Okay.

500
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:46,560
Mr. Din.

501
00:34:49,159 --> 00:34:50,320
Sara?

502
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,800
How did you get here?

503
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:56,520
I came to see a very badly behaved man.

504
00:34:57,760 --> 00:34:59,560
What do you mean? I don't understand.

505
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:04,600
If you wanted to start over with your ex,

506
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:06,640
you could've just told me.

507
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:10,080
- It's not like that, Ms. Sarah--
- Congratulations, Ms. Eyes.

508
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:18,040
That ring looks beautiful on your finger.

509
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:27,160
So, the important thing
you said you were saving up for,

510
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:29,440
turns out

511
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:32,920
it was Ms. Eyes' ring.

512
00:35:34,680 --> 00:35:37,280
- No, that's not--
- I'm ready to divorce for you.

513
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:42,600
Whenever you're ready, just tell me.

514
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:53,840
Why are you still here?
She completely misunderstood everything.

515
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:55,760
- Go after her.
- Follow her, Din.

516
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:57,360
Hurry. Go.

517
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:59,040
Sara.

518
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:31,080
Hey.

519
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:34,600
Hey.

520
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:38,120
- Let me go.
- I won't.

521
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:42,560
I love you.

522
00:36:49,480 --> 00:36:50,960
What did you say?

523
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:55,680
You heard me right.

524
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:02,240
I said…

525
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,480
I love you.

526
00:37:08,240 --> 00:37:09,600
Then what about Ms. Eyes?

527
00:37:10,680 --> 00:37:12,000
I saw you

528
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,440
give her the ring.

529
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:17,200
That wasn't my ring.

530
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:20,600
That ring belongs to Eyes' husband.

531
00:37:27,200 --> 00:37:28,640
The one in this box

532
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:30,240
is yours.

533
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,080
I…

534
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:37,320
I'm so confused right now.

535
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:39,880
Eyes is getting married,

536
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:44,720
so she asked me and Nam to help.
Her husband is overseas.

537
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:49,640
As for this ring…

538
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:57,680
I bought it for you.

539
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:03,840
Then why didn't you tell me?

540
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:06,320
Because I wanted to surprise you.

541
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:08,160
Who would've thought

542
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:10,360
you'd misunderstand this badly?

543
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,880
Anyone would've misunderstood.

544
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:16,280
Even with Baicha's situation, you still--

545
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:34,160
If I ever did anything
that made you doubt me,

546
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,440
I'm sorry.

547
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:39,240
I promise,

548
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:43,120
from now on, there will be
nothing for you to question.

549
